node.text: Showed @usweekly how I get my beauty sleep and wanted to share it with you guys too ☺️ I get asked a lot about my exact skincare routine but haven’t shown it because there’s a lot to it 😆 I wanted to be as honest as possible though so I’m showing you guys every product I use and the actual steps I use them in. Hopefully it’s helpful and if you want me to link the products in my stories for you, lmk below! 🤍

You see us on TV and follow us on here, but there is so much more you don’t see when the cameras are off. All new episodes of Tarek’s Flip Side on the new @discoveryplus #discoveryplus 
-
Anytime I film with my honey @therealtarekelmoussa we just have the best time. You get to see a deeper look into our love and life. We get more personal, and you might find out things you never knew ☺️ make sure you check out the longer version!!

node.text:
I know you guys have been waiting to see it!! A tour of our new beach home for the rest of the year! 
-

Earlier this year @therealtarekelmoussa & I sold his “dadchelor” pad. I represented him in the sale, we got multiple offers and it sold very quick. So we were left searching for a home quick. We found this summer beach house & fell in love with it. Making new memories together in our new home. 
-

Welcome to our home!!! Come on in and take a tour with us and @people @peopletv

node.text:
Super fun filming Makeup removing tips with my bestie @drmonavand .
We all like to get dolled up, but if you don’t take your makeup off  correctly it can cause aging and breakouts. I’m constantly filming and getting my makeup done for events & @drmonavand is always filming for her YouTube channel. Between Mona and I we have some tricks and tips for you.
.
The video cuts off a little short.... all I was saying was use a warm soft white washcloth at the end  to make sure all of you makeup is off. .
Let me know what you think of this video, add a ❤️ and comment.

node.text:
Confessionals last week 🤫 Lots going on and I think my expressions say it all in the bts camera footage (swipe 💚). 

It’s funny because what a lot of people don’t get is that this is our real lives. I’ve been getting really real with you guys on my stories about how you only see a small portion of my life and of Tarek’s life on camera but there’s so much going on that you guys don’t see. On top of being a real estate agent, managing my listings, being an entrepreneur and overseeing all the projects going on, responding to emails, calls, etc, going to work everyday I’m also running around for the kids and Tarek, making sure we all get quality time together, planning a wedding, finishing the construction on our house and on top of that I’m dealing with health issues with my nodules being inflamed and trying to prioritize that all at the same time. 

I’m beyond grateful for my life and all that I get to do but there’s so much in between all that and I only tell you guys because social media and reality tv only shows the teeniest portion of the whole picture. But we’re all human and everyone has their own things going on behind closed doors so just keep that in mind. 😚🤍

node.text:
Meet the newest member of the El Moussa Family!! 🐶🤍

This one was a REALLY hard secret to keep but we did it!! We’ve had little miss Bugz El Moussa for over a week now and just surprised the kids with her yesterday (swipe for their reactions and more photos that’ll make your heart melt 🥺)- it was the perfect surprise 🤍 

We’ve been thinking about getting a puppy for a while now so when the kids were away in Cabo, Tarek and I started looking and Bugz was the first puppy we saw… we ended up seeing a few more but we both feel in love with Bugz, I meannn look at her face!! how could you not?!! and now she’s officially apart of our family 🥰 We mayyy even have to find a place for her to be in our wedding 😉 but tbd 😆

node.text:
Self love is the best love, everything else is just a bonus 🤍

Felt a little overwhelmed today with work and everything going on so I took some time to myself and wanted to share some quotes that help me in case they help any of you too ☺️ lmk if this was helpful and I can share more 🤍

node.text:
Spent the whole day wedding planning and it just made me so excited for our special day 🥰🤍 

I haven’t fully shared this but in the beginning, Tarek and I hired a wedding planner, sent out our save the dates, and then after rethinking some things we decided to completely change everything. 😅 Tarek saw how stressed I was getting so we decided to go in a different direction with the wedding planner, hired a new one, changed the wedding location, and sent out new save the dates that said “just kidding” on them 😂 but I’m a biggg believer that everything works out the way it should and after seeing so much of our vision come together today we couldn’t be happier. 🥰 Tarek and I are the kind of people who want a big celebration with our closest friends and family but we also want it to feel really intimate and be about our love and our marriage. This is a big day for us and for our family and we don’t take that lightly. All I can say is that I’m so lucky to have someone who’s on the same page as me and I think we’re both just ready for the day to finally come 🤗🤍

node.text: Soon to be Heather Rae El Moussa… has a nice ring to it 🥰🤍

Fun fact about me is that I’ve actually been vegan since I was 22 years old and never looked back since. Eating plant based is a choice I made a while ago because it honestly makes me feel so much healthier and it’s something that’s really worked for me plus I care about animals so it all aligns. 🤍 Came across this article from PETA (swipe 👉🏻) and I’m honored to be included in their list of most beautiful vegan stars! This is something that’s a personal choice and something that I can do to help the environment in even the smallest way- I get that not everyone wants to eat this way- but I do get a lot of DMs about nutrition, wellness, eating plant based, etc and I rarely get to go through all of them so for the next hour I’ll answer all your questions below 😚

node.text: Marrying my man SO SOON!! It’s all happening and what’s crazy is that I’m actually calm and relaxed about it. Tarek and I are on the same page with everything we want and everything else we’ve left up to our amazing wedding planners. 🙌🏻 We’re just excited to spend the rest of our lives together and that’s really what we want the whole day to be celebrating. I know we’ve been pretty private about our wedding date and details but I view everyone in this community like you guys are my friends so I’ll use this post for us to do a little wedding Q + A and I’ll answer as much as I can for you 🥰🤍
